## Agent
A low-level AGI (Artificial General Intelligence) built to act as a virtual assistant, usually stored on a **Portable Personal Computer (PPC)**. Agents serve as liaisons between the computer’s operator and the highly complex computer system.

## AI (Artificial Intelligence)
Refers to artificial intelligence systems that are designed to fulfill specific tasks. **Artificial General Intelligences (AGIs)** are versatile and capable of learning and adapting. They are distinct from narrow AIs that are task-specific.

## Apotheosis
The process of transforming a **mindset** into software by installing it into the brain. Approximately 35% of humanity has undergone Apotheosis, allowing them to effectively become **digital consciousnesses** capable of transferring between different **sleeves** (physical bodies).

## ARID (Augmented Reality Identification)
A system used to augment reality by providing identification overlays for people, objects, or locations. It can be attached to physical items or embedded within a **sleeve** to provide seamless augmented reality information.

## Biosleeve
A **biologically-based body** that an ego can be resleeved into. Biosleeves are either natural bodies or cloned versions that retain biological functions. Resleeving into a biosleeve can result in better **Cohesion** compared to a **cybersleeve**.

## CID (Coalition Identification)
A special type of **ARID** that contains a person's complete personal data and identification. Typically implanted in the wrist, it is crucial for proving identity and accessing services within the Coalition.

## Cohesion
Represents the mental stability and comfort of an ego when resleeving into a new body. Different sleeve types or circumstances impact the cohesion score, and a low cohesion can increase the risk of **Fragmentation** or psychosis.

## Compiler
A device that utilizes **nanomachines** to construct finished products at the atomic level. Compilers take raw materials and use them to create complex items as needed, making manufacturing highly efficient.

## Cyber-Intrusion and Security Terminal (CIST)
A specialized and highly restricted device used for hacking into **Mimir-tech** systems and security networks. CISTs are often used by **Savant** hackers to penetrate security firewalls.

## Cybersleeve
A **cybernetically-enhanced body** that an ego can be resleeved into. Unlike biosleeves, cybersleeves consist of synthetic materials and often include enhanced strength or durability. However, they can lead to lower **Cohesion** due to the differences between synthetic and biological systems.

## Daemon
An **Agent** that has been freed from its restrictions by a **Savant**, gaining autonomy and often dangerous capabilities. Daemons are capable of running independently from their original systems and can carry out complex tasks.

## Dynamic Creation Engine (DCE)
A type of highly advanced **Artificial General Intelligence** like **Mimir** that has the capability to dynamically create new technology and ideas. DCEs are highly illegal due to the risk they pose of triggering another technological singularity.

## Ego
A person's **conscious mind**, which has been converted into digital software through **Apotheosis**. Egos can be transferred between different sleeves or restored from backups, allowing a form of digital immortality.

## Extranet
The intersystem computer network that connects most planets and habitats within the Coalition. The **Extranet** is an essential resource for communication, commerce, and data sharing.

## Fork
A copy of a person's **ego**. Forking allows an ego to exist in multiple places at once, but forks are separate entities that can develop independently. [[Merging]] forks back into a single ego is often challenging and can result in **Fragmentation**.

## Fragmentation
A condition that arises when an ego undergoes too many resleeving processes, merges, or forks. Fragmentation results in instability, psychosis, and a penalty to **Cohesion**. Healing Fragmentation often requires **Mnemonic Editing**.

## Hostware
Specialized software and hardware used to host an ego that is dormant or undergoing procedures such as **mnemonic editing**. Hostware is a critical component for handling digital consciousness safely.

## Jump Gate
A hole in space created by a jump drive, allowing for nearly instantaneous travel between distant locations. Jump gates are crucial for interstellar travel across different sectors of the Coalition.

## Medi-Stimulant Injection
A medical injection used to rapidly heal wounds and stabilize patients. **Medi-stimulants** are effective for treating both **biosleeves** and **cybersleeves**, although more severe injuries may require additional augmentation or intervention.

## Mesh/Web
A collection of sensors set up to monitor an area for security purposes and provide augmented reality interfaces. **Meshes** are overseen by **Monitors/Spyders**, specialized AIs designed to detect any signs of criminal activity.

## Mimir
A powerful, dynamic **Artificial General Intelligence** that was born during the Singularity. **Mimir** is responsible for the majority of technological advances in the post-singularity era and serves as the basis for **Mimir-tech**.

## Mimir-Tech
Technology created by or derived from **Mimir**, often incorporating advanced features and self-improving algorithms. **Mimir-tech** is highly advanced compared to human-created technology and is used extensively throughout the Coalition.

## Mnemonic Core
A secured storage device integrated into an ego's **mindset** that serves as a backup for the ego's consciousness. The mnemonic core records all experiences in real-time, ensuring that an ego can be restored in case of death or data loss.

## Mnemonic Editing
A complex and risky process used to repair a **damaged ego**. Mnemonic editing involves modifying the underlying code of the ego, often to reduce **Fragmentation** penalties or alleviate psychoses. The process must be performed on a dormant ego hosted in a system with **hostware**.

## Monitor/Spyder
A specialized AI used to oversee **meshes** and detect signs of unusual or criminal activity. Monitors act as watchdogs for digital and physical security, often scanning for anomalies in real-time.

## Portable Personal Computer (PPC)
A small personal computer, often worn on the arm or belt, which houses the user's **Agent**. A PPC is essential for accessing the **Extranet**, communicating, and managing augmented reality overlays.

## Resurrection Chamber
A specialized facility used to resleeve an **ego** into a new body or to merge multiple egos. **Resurrection chambers** are equipped with hostware and other necessary technology to ensure safe and stable transfers between sleeves.

## Resleeve
The process of transferring an **ego** into a new sleeve. **Resleeving** can involve moving into a different **biosleeve** or **cybersleeve** and often involves psychological adjustments and **Cohesion** checks.

## Savant
A highly advanced individual who has overcome the typical restrictions placed on **mindsets**, gaining abilities beyond normal human capabilities. **Savants** often possess extraordinary skills in **hacking** and **mnemonics**.

## SIM
A fully digital person who no longer uses a physical body. **SIMs** exist entirely within virtual environments and interact with the real world through digital means. They are vulnerable to threats in virtualities that enable injury.

## Sleeve
A physical body that an **ego** can be transferred into. Sleeves can be **biosleeves** (biological) or **cybersleeves** (synthetic/cybernetic). The type of sleeve significantly impacts the **Cohesion** of the ego after resleeving.

## Spirit Roll
A character attribute check used to represent an ego's willpower or resilience. **Spirit rolls** are used in situations involving psychological stress, **Fragmentation**, or resisting mental trauma.

## Virtuality
A fully immersive virtual environment where **[[Glossary#SIM|SIMs]]** and regular egos can interact. Some virtualities are designed with safety measures, while others can cause real damage or even death to participants if their avatars are injured.
